        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 9:43PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 943 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 11 miles southwest of Octavia to 17 miles
northwest of Broken Bow. Movement was east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Plunketville, Smithville, Hochatown, Watson, Bethel, Battiest, Mount
Herman, and Sherwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
